        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(opencode-go): treat block-boundary SSE events as liveness for idle timer",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nOpenCode Go sends block-boundary SSE events (text_end, thinking_end, toolcall_start, toolcall_end) between content blocks. The stalled-stream liveness wrapper only recognized text_delta/thinking_delta/toolcall_delta as progress, causing premature timeouts on slow-but-live connections.\n\n## Changes\n\n`extensions/opencode-go/stream-termination.ts`: Add 4 event types to the liveness predicate.\n\n`extensions/opencode-go/stream-termination.test.ts`: Add regression test verifying all 4 boundary events reset the idle timer.\n\n## Evidence\n\n```\npnpm exec vitest run extensions/opencode-go/\n  Test Files  5 passed (5)\n       Tests  28 passed (28)\n```\n\n**Label**: bug\n_AI-assisted._",
